title: Mr Wicker's Window version 2
creator: Carley Dawson
description: LibriVox recording of Mr Wicker's Window, by Carley Dawson. Read by Arthur Piantadosi When Christopher Mason walked into Mr. Wicker's antique shop, he had no idea he would soon be embarking on a marvellous journey to China to find a wonderful tree made of jewels. He had no idea that Mr. Wicker was a magician and could travel through time. And that the tree was sought by others, not least among them the murderous Claggett Chew, a merchant in port and a pirate on the high seas, who also had knowledge of magic. But before Chris succeeded in quest, he would know of all these things and more. And of Mr. Wicker's friends, the sailor Ned Cilley, Becky Boozer, and the African boy Amos, changed from wood to flesh. And Christopher Mason would never be same, after. (Introduction by Arthur Piantadosi) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. Download M4B (160MB) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: Librivox;audiobook;children;fiction;magic;pirates
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
Mr. Wicker is a time-travelling wizard who finds a protege after some searching to help in the past.  

The premise is sound, but I just didn't care for the story, it is not my genre I guess.  

The reader is very good.  He is expressive, and clearly gets into the story line.  He stumbles a little here and there, but his enthusiasm more than makes up for it.  

I have to say, I really wanted to like this story, but it just wasn't to my liking.  Kudos to the reader tho, I will be looking for other books he read.
